The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                            Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Feb. 7: Commerce minister Kamal Nath is in favour of lifting the land cap of 5,000 hectares on special economic zones (SEZs) as many states are in need of large-sized SEZs. There are some states which want large SEZs. One cannot have a port SEZ in Madhya Pradesh. Likewise one cannot have the same policy in Kerala and Madhya Pradesh. There cannot be a one-size-fits-all policy for all states, Nath said.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 7: Tata Chemicals has proposed a sale of part of its stake in Tata Investment Corporation to holding company Tata Sons for up to Rs 325 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 7: Wheat output in India is estimated to decline by 1 million tonnes to 74.81 million tonnes during this year. The country has been importing the foodgrain for the last two years to meet the demand.                             
	 London/Mumbai, Feb. 7: Ranbaxy has received a tentative US approval to sell a generic form of AstraZenecas ulcer pill Nexium, damaging confidence in the Anglo-Swedish drugmakers future profits.                            
	 Brussels, Feb. 7: InBev and AnheuserBusch of the US are in talks for a merger of the two, Belgian business magazine Trends reported.                                                                                                                           
